First factor everything:

\[
\frac{y^2-36}{2y^2+11y-6}
\;\Big|\;
y^2-36=(y-6)(y+6),
\quad
2y^2+11y-6=(2y-1)(y+6),
\]
\[
\frac{2y^2-2y-60}{8y-4}
\;\Big|\;
2y^2-2y-60=2(y^2-y-30)=2(y-6)(y+5),
\quad
8y-4=4(2y-1).
\]

So the original expression is
\[
\frac{(y-6)(y+6)}{(2y-1)(y+6)}
\;\Big/\;
\frac{2(y-6)(y+5)}{4(2y-1)}
\;=\;
\frac{(y-6)(y+6)}{(2y-1)(y+6)}
\;\times\;
\frac{4(2y-1)}{2(y-6)(y+5)}.
\]
Cancel \((y+6),\,2y-1,\,(y-6)\) to get
\[
\frac{4}{2(y+5)}=\frac{2}{\,y+5\,}.
\]
