First write  
  f(x)=\frac{15x^2}{3x^2+33x}
        =\frac{15x^2}{3x(x+11)}
        =\frac{5x}{x+11},  
and  
  g(x)=\frac{5x-5}{x^2+9x-22}
       =\frac{5(x-1)}{(x+11)(x-2)}.  

Then  
  R(x)=\frac{f(x)}{g(x)}
       =\frac{\displaystyle\frac{5x}{x+11}}{\displaystyle\frac{5(x-1)}{(x+11)(x-2)}}
       =\frac{5x}{x+11}\cdot\frac{(x+11)(x-2)}{5(x-1)}
       =\frac{x(x-2)}{x-1}.  

So  
  R(x)=\frac{x(x-2)}{x-1}\,,  
with the exclusions (where f or g is undefined or g=0):  
  x\neq -11,\;0,\;2,\;1.
